  "comments": {
    "emnapi": "@emnapi/core and @emnapi/runtime are pinned here (direct devDeps) and in overrides solely to stabilise the lock. They are peer deps of @napi-rs/wasm-runtime, bundled inside the optional @tailwindcss/oxide-wasm32-wasi WASM fallback. Left alone, npm's ideal tree upgrades the ^1.7.1 peer range to the latest registry release (1.11.1, published after the lock), which Linux `npm ci` then reports as missing — EUSAGE. The override caps the version at the 1.10.0 the tarball actually bundles; the direct devDeps force a root entry into the lock on every platform (Windows prunes the optional-only subtree, so without this the lock regenerates incomplete). The WASM fallback is never used on the native Linux/Windows oxide binaries."
  },
  "overrides": {
    "@emnapi/core": "1.10.0",
    "@emnapi/runtime": "1.10.0"
  }
}
